#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/bundle-barrel-imports.md
M|rules|title: Avoid Barrel File Imports
M|rules|impact: CRITICAL
M|rules|impactDescription: 200-800ms import cost, slow builds
M|rules|tags: bundle, imports, tree-shaking, barrel-files, performance
M|rules|Import directly from source files instead of barrel files to avoid loading thousands of unused modules. **Barrel files** are entry points that re-export multiple modules (e.g., `index.js` that does `e
M|rules|Popular icon and component libraries can have **up to 10,000 re-exports** in their entry file. For many React packages, **it takes 200-800ms just to import them**, affecting both dev speed and prd col
M|rules|**Why tree-shaking doesn't help:** When a library is marked as external (not bundled), the bundler can't optimize it. If you bundle it to enable tree-shaking, builds become substantially slower analyz
M|rules|**Incorrect (imports entire library):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import { Check, X, Menu } from 'lucide-react'
M|rules|// Loads 1,583 modules, takes ~2.8s extra in dev
M|rules|// Runtime cost: 200-800ms on every cold start
M|rules|import { Button, TextField } from '@mui/material'
M|rules|// Loads 2,225 modules, takes ~4.2s extra in dev
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct - Next.js 13.5+ (recommended):**
M|rules|```js
M|rules|// next.config.js - automatically optimizes barrel imports at build time
M|rules|module.exports = {
M|rules|experimental: {
M|rules|optimizePackageImports: ['lucide-react', '@mui/material']
M|rules|}
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// Keep the standard imports - Next.js transforms them to direct imports
M|rules|import { Check, X, Menu } from 'lucide-react'
M|rules|// Full TypeScript support, no manual path wrangling
M|rules|```
M|rules|This is the recommended approach because it preserves TypeScript type safety and editor autocompletion while still eliminating the barrel import cost.
M|rules|**Correct - Direct imports (non-Next.js projects):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import Button from '@mui/material/Button'
M|rules|import TextField from '@mui/material/TextField'
M|rules|// Loads only what you use
M|rules|```
M|rules|> **TypeScript warning:** Some libraries (notably `lucide-react`) don't ship `.d.ts` files for their deep import paths. Importing from `lucide-react/dist/esm/icons/check` resolves to an implicit `any`
M|rules|These optimizations provide 15-70% faster dev boot, 28% faster builds, 40% faster cold starts, and significantly faster HMR.
M|rules|Libraries commonly affected: `lucide-react`, `@mui/material`, `@mui/icons-material`, `@tabler/icons-react`, `react-icons`, `@headlessui/react`, `@radix-ui/react-*`, `lodash`, `ramda`, `date-fns`, `rxj
M|rules|Reference: [How we optimized package imports in Next.js](https://vercel.com/blog/how-we-optimized-package-imports-in-next-js)